    • Field Detail

      • PENDING

        public static final int PENDING
        Special constant to augment those in TaskStatusInfo. Used when a slave talks back its master at the time that a task is added to its executor pool for execution. At this point it might get queued rather than executed. Once it is executed, the slave will tell the master that it is now executing (TaskStatusInfo.PROCESSING).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • STOPPED

        public static final int STOPPED
        Special constant to augment those in TaskStatusInfo. Used when a task has been stopped (successfully). Only applies to the current execution of a given task. Scheduled tasks will still execute again at the next scheduled time.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
